LEX Escrow.

"Payer" is a person.
"Payee" is a person.
"Agent" is a person.
"Amount" is an amount.

The Payer pays an Amount into escrow, appoints the Payee, appoints the Agent.

CLAUSE: Pay Out.
The Agent may pay the escrow to the Payee.

CLAUSE: Pay Back.
The Agent may pay the escrow to the Payer.

